      <!-- Slide 4: Special Andean Ingredients -->
      <div class="slide">
        <h2 class="slide-title">Special Andean Ingredients</h2>
        <div class="slide-content">
          <p>Pachamanca uses many traditional Andean foods you might not have seen before:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Habas</strong>: Large fava beans that grow well in mountain environments</li>
            <li><strong>Ollucos</strong>: Colorful tubers (similar to potatoes) with bright yellow or pink flesh</li>
            <li><strong>Choclos</strong>: Large-kernel Andean corn that's less sweet than the corn you might be used to</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="slide-image-container">
            <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/56/Pachamanca_de_res.JPG/640px-Pachamanca_de_res.JPG" alt="Traditional Andean ingredients" class="slide-image">
